    <stitle>BRAKE COMPONENTS: This Service Manual Section should be used for reference only. For more current service
        information on all components go to the Bendix website from the ISIS Suppliers menu and refer to the Service
        Data Sheets. - PRESSURE PROTECTION VALVE - MAINTENANCE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="1">
        <title>MAINTENANCE</title>
        <para>Once each year or 100,000 miles (160,000 km), remove the pressure protection valve (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0400215">Figure 15</hotlnk>
            ), disassemble it and clean all parts.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0400215" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0400215" filename="../figg04/G0400215.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 15. Pressure Protection Valve - Cross Section</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. VENT HOLE</callout1>
                <callout1>2. UPPER BODY</callout1>
                <callout1>3. DIAPHRAGM</callout1>
                <callout1>4. AIR FLOW</callout1>
                <callout1>5. LOWER BODY</callout1>
                <callout1>6. SPRING CAP</callout1>
                <callout1>7. SPRING</callout1>
                <callout1>8. SHIM</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>Replace the diaphragm if it is worn or deteriorated.</para>
    </svcproc>
